cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.DC, cs.IT, cs.CC 

The paper deals with secure computation protocols and their application to secure machine learning inference. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the protocols, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The application of the protocols to machine learning inference suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible category. Finally, the paper presents protocols for secure 3-party computation, which could also fall under cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
